Cross dresser Idris Okuneye aka Bobrisky has addressed his fellow co-hustlers. Bobrisky, addressing all the prostitutes, said they must take cognisance of the failing exchange rate. He claimed a dollar is N640 so those in the trade should consider ncreasing their price card.   Davido joins JayJay Okocha at 2022 CAF awards     Tiwa Savage performs at 2022 CAF awards     Mr P replies to allegation of N7,000 fraud   According to Bob: “All the oloshos in the house, our price don high o. Let’s update our price card. $1 is now 640.” The Instagram celebrity revealed he has cancelled short times transaction, noting he would only engage in weekend dealings. “As a matter of fact no more short time. Na weekend things now,” he clarified. As of the time of this report, though Bobrisky claimed a dollar exchanges for N640, checks by The Nation revealed the exchange rate for dollar to naira at Lagos Parallel Market (Black Market), players buy a dollar for N590 and sell at N620 on Wednesday, July 20, 2022, according to sources at Bureau De Change (BDC).